│ only if their pointer operand is not found in SafePtrs:\n  if (auto *LI =     │
│ dyn_cast<LoadInst>(&I)) {\n    if                                             │
│ (!SafePtrs.count(LI->getPointerOperand()))\n      MaskedOp.insert(LI);\n      │
│ continue;\n  }\nSafePtrs collects pointer operands considered dereferenceable │
│ (fault-safe) either because they appear in non-predicated blocks or proved    │
│ dereferenceable via SCEV/dereferenceability queries. This reasoning ignores   │
│ the possibility that, after vectorization and predicate widening, operands    │
